Example Breakdown BaseClassNormally Dota chooses the C++ class to connect to an ability by looking at the ability name (in this case "fx_test_ability"). If you'd like to force Dota to use a different C++ class, the BaseClass key will do that. In this example we're using the ability_datadriven class to connect to the data driven ability system. It's p ossible to use this key to connect to any other existing ability code to make a new variant of an existing Dota 2 ability with different settings for whatever that ability exposes to keyvalues.
Found at
https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/Dota_2_Workshop_Tools/Scripting/Abilities_Data_Driven
